						               													<description>In Mattock, you play miners digging corridors through the rock. You can&amp;rsquo;t dig too closely together though, or the mine will collapse. To win, trap your opponent so they run out of space to mine.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Playing the Game:&amp;#10;On your turn, take these 3 steps in order:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#145;&amp;#160; Mine&amp;#10;Place 1 tile on an open space next to, or connected by other tiles to, at least 1 of your miners. Opponent&amp;rsquo;s miners block connections.&amp;#10;To prevent the mine from collapsing, the tile must not touch:&amp;#10;     &amp;bull;    more than 3 other tiles;&amp;#10;     &amp;bull;    a tile which already touches 3 other tiles.&amp;#10;If you have any miners which were removed on previous turns, place 1 of them on this tile.&amp;#10;      If you cannot Mine, you lose the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#145;&amp;#161; Move&amp;#10;You may choose to move any 1 of your miners to a tile connected to it. You do not have to move.&amp;#10;You may move through your own miners, but opponent&amp;rsquo;s miners block your path.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#145;&amp;#162; Remove&amp;#10;Remove all opponent miners that are now both:&amp;#10;     &amp;bull;    Not connected to another opponent miner;&amp;#10;     &amp;bull;    Connected to 2 or more of your miners.&amp;#10;Your opponent takes the removed miner(s) and will place 1 back on the board on their turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
